This paper deals with algorithms and complexity results for a specific type of logic program, namely Hybrid Probabilistic Programs (HPPs). The paper discusses the computation of ground consequences, entailment, and consistency for HPPs. These topics are relevant to several subfields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), programming languages (cs.PL), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
